* Use GL_TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY to combine the materials into texture arrays.
  This will DRASTICALLY reduce the number of glDrawElements() calls, particularly
  for translucent Blocks.

* Make fluids flow.

* Make crouching prevent the player from walking off cliffs.

* Fix the weird darkened corners on Nvidia chipsets.

* Make new parts of the world automatically load.

* Sound!

* Gaussian blurring when underwater:
    http://www.gamedev.net/page/resources/_//feature/fprogramming/opengl-frame-buffer-object-101-r2331
    http://www.gamerendering.com/2008/10/11/gaussian-blur-filter-shader/

* Port to Windows.

* Python scripting.

* Multiplayer.

* Fix nasty crash:
    tpp.c:63: __pthread_tpp_change_priority: Assertion `new_prio == -1 || (new_prio >= __sched_fifo_min_prio && new_prio <= __sched_fifo_max_prio)' failed.
